Description: Type: Sagittal, Side: Left otolith. Shape: elliptic, crenate dorsal margin and crenate ventral margin. Sulcus acusticus: heterosulcoid, ostial, supramedian. Ostium: funnel-like, shorter than the cauda. Cauda: tubular, strongly curved. Anterior region: double peaked, rostrum long, broad, pointed, antirostrum short, narrow, sharply pointed, excisura wide with an acute, deep notch. Posterior region: irregular.
